<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<RelativeLayout
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#F1F6F9"
    tools:context=".lessons.Lesson17">

    <androidx.appcompat.widget.Toolbar
        android:id="@+id/toolbar"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="?attr/actionBarSize"
        android:background="#F1F6F9">
        <Button
            android:id="@+id/btn_back"
            android:background="@null"
            android:drawableStart="@drawable/btn_back"
            android:layout_width="48dp"
            android:layout_height="?attr/actionBarSize"
            android:contentDescription="@string/back_button"/>
        <TextView
            android:text="Lesson 17"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:layout_gravity="center"
            android:gravity="center"
            android:textColor="@color/black"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
    </androidx.appcompat.widget.Toolbar>

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_below="@+id/toolbar"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content">
        <LinearLayout
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content">
            <androidx.cardview.widget.CardView
                app:cardCornerRadius="16dp"
                app:cardElevation="0dp"
                android:layout_marginHorizontal="16dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                <LinearLayout
                    android:orientation="vertical"
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="match_parent">
                    <LinearLayout
                        android:orientation="horizontal"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                        <TextView
                            android:text="Quarter 1 â€“ Module 17:\nDifferentiating Repeating from Terminating and Non Terminating Decimal Quotient"
                            android:textSize="16sp"
                            android:paddingHorizontal="10dp"
                            android:paddingBottom="10dp"
                            android:textColor="@color/black"
                            android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_semi_bold"
                            android:layout_width="0dp"
                            android:layout_weight="1"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                        <Button
                            android:id="@+id/btn_tts"
                            android:text="Read"
                            android:textAlignment="textStart"
                            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                            android:background="@drawable/btn_secondary_button"
                            android:drawableStart="@drawable/ic_mic_secondary"
                            android:drawablePadding="10dp"
                            android:paddingHorizontal="10dp"
                            android:layout_width="0dp"
                            android:layout_weight=".5"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                    </LinearLayout>

                    <ImageView
                        android:background="@color/light_gray"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="1dp"/>

                    <TextView
                        android:id="@+id/tv_lessons_description_one"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                        android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_regular"
                        android:padding="10dp"
                        android:text="Differentiating between repeating and terminating decimal quotients:\n\nWhen dividing two numbers, the quotient can result in different types of decimal representations: terminating decimals, non-terminating decimals, or repeating decimals.\n\nTerminating Decimal: A terminating decimal is a decimal that ends after a finite number of digits. When dividing, the remainder becomes zero, and the division process stops. The quotient is a complete number without any recurring digits.\n\nExample: Divide 3 by 2. The quotient is 1.5, which terminates after the digit 5. There are no recurring or repeating digits, so the decimal is terminating.\n\nNon-Terminating Decimal: A non-terminating decimal is a decimal that continues indefinitely without repeating a pattern of digits. The division process continues infinitely, without the remainder becoming zero.\n\nExample: Divide 1 by 3. The quotient is approximately 0.3333333... The digit 3 repeats indefinitely without any specific pattern. Since the division process never stops, the decimal is non-terminating.\n\nRepeating Decimal: A repeating decimal is a decimal that has a recurring pattern of digits. The division process continues indefinitely, but a specific set of digits repeats over and over again.\n\nExample: Divide 2 by 3. The quotient is 0.666666... In this case, the digit 6 repeats indefinitely, indicating a recurring pattern. The decimal is called a repeating decimal.\n\nDifferentiating between these types of decimals is important, especially when dealing with precise calculations or when representing fractions as decimals. Terminating decimals are straightforward, while non-terminating decimals can be approximated using rounding. Repeating decimals are usually represented by placing a bar over the recurring digits." />
                    <TextView
                        android:text="Example:"
                        android:padding="10dp"
                        android:textColor="@color/black"
                        android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_semi_bold"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                    <ImageView
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="200dp"
                        android:layout_gravity="center"
                        android:contentDescription="example"
                        android:src="@drawable/smple_mod17" />

                </LinearLayout>
            </androidx.cardview.widget.CardView>

            <HorizontalScrollView
